# C++ CMake Project Template — Cursor AI Rules

## CRITICAL: Read Before Acting

This repository has **full automation tooling**. Before writing any code or CMake:
1. Check if `scripts/toollib.py` or `scripts/toolsolution.py` can do it
2. Run `python3 scripts/toollib.py --help` to see available commands
3. Use existing tools — do NOT re-implement library scaffolding, preset management, etc.

## Validation (run after EVERY change)

```bash
python3 scripts/build.py check --no-sync
```

## Library Management

```bash
python3 scripts/toollib.py add <name>               # normal lib
python3 scripts/toollib.py add <name> --header-only # header-only
python3 scripts/toollib.py add <name> --interface   # interface target
python3 scripts/toollib.py deps <name> --add <dep>  # local dep
python3 scripts/toollib.py deps <name> --add-url https://github.com/org/repo@tag  # external
python3 scripts/toollib.py export <name>            # find_package() support
python3 scripts/toollib.py info <name>              # show details
python3 scripts/toollib.py doctor                   # health check
```

## Project Management

```bash
python3 scripts/toolsolution.py target list
python3 scripts/toolsolution.py preset add --compiler gcc --type debug --link static --arch x86_64
python3 scripts/toolsolution.py toolchain add --name stm32 --template arm-none-eabi --cpu cortex-m4 --gen-preset
python3 scripts/toolsolution.py upgrade-std --std 20
python3 scripts/toolsolution.py doctor
```

## Structure Rules

- Every library in `libs/` must have: `CMakeLists.txt`, `README.md`, `include/<n>/`, `docs/`
- Normal libs also need: `src/<n>.cpp`, `tests/unit/<n>/`
- All targets use target-scoped CMake — no global flags
- Never touch `external/` directly (managed by toollib/toolsolution)
- Never remove presets from `CMakePresets.json`

## C++ Build Info

```cpp
#include "ProjectInfo.h"
BUILD_INFO_PRINT_ALL(std::cout, my_namespace);
#if FEATURE_BOOST
    // Boost available
#endif
```

## Forbidden

- Re-implementing library scaffolding (use toollib.py)
- Global CMake flags
- Editing external/
- Breaking existing tests
- Partial/placeholder code
